I’m trying to use PathPlanner to create an auto sequence called DineNDash. I have created it with PathPlanner, and the auto file is in the deploy folder. However, when i use the auto, it only runs the first named command in the sequence, and I’m not sure why. Here is the project file:GitHub - bdog222/GriffinDisco

The first command in DineNDash is OuttakeStart. The isFinished() currently only return false, so the command never ends. You will need to end the OuttakeStart command in order for the next command in the sequence to start.

Same problem with IntakeStart and IntakeStop.

I use it for our shooter, as we don’t have a definite way to know if the note has fully exited it yet.

Just gotta have some way of ending the command so that the next command in the sequence can start.
